					<span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/dr-whitney" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(5252186); return false;"  ><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=5252186&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1610223644" alt="Dr Whitney" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=5252186)"/></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/dr-whitney" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(5252186); return false;" >Dr Whitney</a></span> <span class="odate time_1590025052 format_%25e%20%25b%20%25Y%2C%20%25H%3A%25M%7Cagohover">21 May 2020 01:37</span>
														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-4655809">
									

<p>I hope you enjoy this little project of mine. I have spent the last few months working on this and I think I am happy with the final product. This started as only 4 pages and is around 15 wow. This is honestly the first comic I have finished since I don't count my first post which was only a page long.</p>
<p>For this idea, I wanted to explore the idea of justice and create a situation where there is no easy answer. I didn't want to tell the reader what was right or wrong I wanted you to decide and I hope I accomplished that.</p>
<p>Thank you Alces_alces, Magic8Ball04, AnActualCrow , cybersqyd, Sonderance, Dr Remember, Einer von Rabe, Luvview, and anyone else who I may be forgetting. You guys have helped me out so much and I don't know what I can do to thank you! You guys are amazing writers and your help means so much to me. :)</p>

							</div>

								
					
