															</div>
				<div class="info">
					<span class="printuser deleted" data-id="3146689"><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/common--images/avatars/default/a16.png" alt=""/>(account deleted)</span> <span class="odate time_1590073030 format_%25e%20%25b%20%25Y%2C%20%25H%3A%25M%7Cagohover">21 May 2020 14:57</span>
														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-4656783">
									

<p>I gotta somewhat second sirpudding on this, although my main problem with this lies in a different aspect. The art is nice, but the presented story and the presentation itself lack any depth or interesting details whatsoever. The characters' dialogue isn't believable and the way they interact at times feels as if it's a comedic story, which doesn't connect well with the supposedly serious dramatic moment the tale is trying to achieve (and using antropomorphic lizard as a researcher doesn't help here either).</p>
<p>The story and characters are only used to present a pretty blunt and simplistic dilemma (whether should take revenge or act professionally) which is more about the character's own personal demons and inability to fight them off than about being morally right/wrong. The story didn't provide much development for the character itself or the person they've decided to murder, so the drama, for the most part, falls flat.</p>
<p>As I said, I really dig the visual part. But since it's a writing site, I see the writing itself as the most crucial part of a tale, even if it's done in such an unusual format. I don't think anything here besides the art was that good, and for that reason it's a downvote from me.</p>

							</div>

								
